Description: Fragment of slightly concave rim of Attic black-glazed pottery cup or phiale. Wholly glazed save for reserved band at top, inside. Incised inscription on outside.
Bibliographic references: Edgar 1898/1899 / Excavations at Naukratis. B: The Inscribed and Painted Pottery (no. 70)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 701, no. 593)
Höckmann & Möller 2006 / The Hellenion at Naukratis: Questions and Observations (14, fig. 7,4)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1717)
